Chrysanthemum coccineum

   [4523.jpg]
    Authority   Willd.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Asteridae:Asterales:Compositae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 4523

   Notes
   SOURCES (C. coccineum Willd.)
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 258 [USE]
   Duke J 1975 pp 11 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Purseglove J 1974 pp 58 [USE]
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial herb.
   COMMON NAMES
   Persian insect-flower.
   FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonym: C. roseum. Persian insect-flower can be grown in
   the tropics above 1000 m in elevation. Its insect toxicity is less than
   the Dalmatian plant.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
